212 Ernst Steinicke, Peter Cede, and Ulrike Fliesser

Northern Friuli, however, reveals that the phenomenon of amenity migration can also 
occur, albeit to a lesser extent, in areas that have embraced tourism only cautiously, 
if at all. The explanation here can likewise be found in public financing and assist­
ance (cf. Steinicke 1991): After the 1976 earthquake, a comprehensive reconstruction 
program was implemented, thanks to support at regional, national and international 
levels. As a result of this initiative, an abundant supply of suitable housing is still 
available in the Friulian mountains, which otherwise suffer from the problem of severe 
demographic over-aging.

